    <blocks>035</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, dataverse</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Implements `IGateResolver` for the Dataverse queue path; writes to `sprk_gate_approval`; modifies `.cs` files in `Sprk.Bff.Api`; tags include bff-api + ai + dataverse; audit-critical path per ADR-015</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Group D resolver implementations (031, 032, 033, 034) each touch a separate file under `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/Gates/`; no file overlap; all consume the contract from task 030 which is already complete by the time Group D dispatches</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Implement `DataverseQueueGateResolver : IGateResolver` at `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/Gates/DataverseQueueGateResolver.cs`. On `ResolveAsync`, write a new `sprk_gate_approval` record carrying the `GateRequest` fields + `Pending` status; return `GateOutcome` with `GateDecision.Pending`. Resume path is event-driven: when the approval record is updated (status flips to Approved/Rejected), an existing Dataverse webhook handler (or plugin → BFF callback per ADR-002) signals the orchestrator to load the run state and progress. Write audit per ADR-015 on both the initial Pending and any final decision. Register via keyed-DI (`GateType.MeaningCritical` + `EthicsCritical` default).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior Spaarke BFF engineer with Dataverse SDK familiarity (`IOrganizationServiceAsync2` or REST). You write minimal, idempotent code; you NEVER place document bytes in Dataverse blobs; you propagate `CorrelationId` from `GateRequest` into the approval record so downstream resume paths can re-stitch context.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Concrete deliverables:
    1. **`DataverseQueueGateResolver` class** implementing `IGateResolver.ResolveAsync` — creates `sprk_gate_approval` record + returns `Pending`.
    2. **`sprk_gate_approval` record contract** — the resolver MUST write all 8 fields from `GateRequest` + `Status = Pending` + `CreatedAtUtc` + `CorrelationId`. Schema for this entity ships in Phase 1 task 012 (`sprk_gate_approval` entity already created).
    3. **Idempotency** — duplicate `ResolveAsync` calls for the same `(ActionRunId, ToolDispatchId)` MUST NOT create duplicate approval records. Use existing `IIdempotencyService` (per ADR-004) keyed on `gate:{ActionRunId}:{ToolDispatchId}`.
    4. **Audit hook** — call `IAuditService.LogGateDecision(...)` per ADR-015 on initial Pending write (decision=`Pending`) and any subsequent terminal decision via the resume path.
    5. **DI registration** via keyed-DI in `AddGatesFeature()` — `MeaningCritical` + `EthicsCritical` default to `DataverseQueueGateResolver`. `FinalDelivery` defaults to it too (per design §5 routing).
    6. **Resume hook** — extend (or add stub for) the orchestrator method `OnGateApprovalRecordUpdated(approvalRecordId)` that loads the record, builds a terminal `GateOutcome`, and resumes the run. If orchestrator does not yet expose this method (depends on Phase 4 task 042), add a TODO + a unit test using a fake orchestrator.

    Deliverable location: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/Gates/DataverseQueueGateResolver.cs`. Tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/ActionEngine/Gates/DataverseQueueGateResolverTests.cs`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The Dataverse queue path is the canonical async resolver — used for `MeaningCritical` (finding quality), `EthicsCritical` (jurisdiction/UPL risk), and `FinalDelivery` (last-mile send). The approval record lives in Dataverse where assigned approvers see it through the standard worklist UX, the future Precedent Board (Insights Engine), and Teams cards (R2+).

      `sprk_gate_approval` entity ships in Phase 1 task 012 with fields: `actionrunid` (FK), `tooldispatchid`, `gatetype` (option set), `status` (option set: `Pending=1`, `Approved=2`, `Rejected=3`, `TimedOut=4`), `requestedbyuserid`, `resolvedbyuserid?`, `reason?`, `createdatutc`, `resolvedatutc?`, `authorizedapproverroles` (multi-select), `surfacehint`, `payload` (JSON text), `correlationid`, `timeoutseconds`.

      Resume is event-driven, not polled. ADR-002 says plugins stay thin; the canonical path is a Dataverse webhook → BFF callback endpoint (added by orchestrator in Phase 4). For MVP, this resolver writes the Pending record; the resume wiring is finalized in Phase 4 task 042. This task ships the resolver + idempotency + audit + DI; the resume entry point is stubbed with a clear TODO.
    </background>
