  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: working tree clean, branch `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, task 030 ✅ in TASK-INDEX. Load knowledge. Declare RIGOR LEVEL: FULL.</step>
    <step order="1">Read task 030's `IGateResolver` contract + `GateRequest` / `GateOutcome` records. Read `notes/decisions/030-gateresolver-contract.md` for any contract decisions (keyed-DI shape, audit obligation).</step>
    <step order="2">Confirm `sprk_gate_approval` entity exists (task 012). If schema gaps: stop and signal back to task 012 owner. Otherwise proceed.</step>
    <step order="3">Create `DataverseQueueGateResolver.cs` — ctor injects `IDataverseClient`, `IAuditService`, `IIdempotencyService`, `ILogger&lt;DataverseQueueGateResolver&gt;`. Implement `ResolveAsync`: idempotency check → write `sprk_gate_approval` Pending record → audit log → return `GateOutcome` with `Pending`.</step>
    <step order="4">Map `GateRequest.Payload` (`JsonElement?`) to the `payload` field as serialized JSON text. Map `AuthorizedApproverRoles` to the multi-select. Preserve `CorrelationId` on the record.</step>
    <step order="5">Register via keyed-DI in `AddGatesFeature()` (extending `AddActionEngineModule.cs`): `services.AddKeyedScoped&lt;IGateResolver, DataverseQueueGateResolver&gt;(GateType.MeaningCritical); ...EthicsCritical; ...FinalDelivery;`. ADR-010 budget check: 3 keyed registrations consume 3 slots.</step>
    <step order="6">Add resume stub method on the orchestrator (or stand-alone `IGateResumeHandler` if orchestrator-side method not yet in scope per Phase 4 timing): `OnGateApprovalRecordUpdated(Guid approvalRecordId)`. Stub implementation: load record, build `GateOutcome`, audit, log TODO for Phase 4 to wire to actual run resumption.</step>
    <step order="7">Write unit tests in `DataverseQueueGateResolverTests.cs`:
      (a) `ResolveAsync_HappyPath_WritesPendingRecordAndReturnsPending` — assert `IDataverseClient.CreateAsync` called once with correct entity logical name + fields.
      (b) `ResolveAsync_DuplicateCall_IsIdempotent` — second call with same `(ActionRunId, ToolDispatchId)` returns same outcome without creating a second record.
      (c) `ResolveAsync_Audits_OnPendingWrite` — `IAuditService.LogGateDecision` called with `GateDecision.Pending`.
      (d) `ResolveAsync_PreservesCorrelationId` — record carries the request's correlationId.
      (e) `OnGateApprovalRecordUpdated_Approved_BuildsApprovedOutcomeAndAudits`.</step>
    <step order="8">Build + run unit tests: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0; `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` passes new tests.</step>
    <step order="9">Measure publish-size delta. Expected &lt; 0.1 MB. Record in `notes/measurements/031-publish-size-delta.md`.</step>
    <step order="9.5">Run quality gates: `code-review` (idempotency correctness, audit ordering: AUDIT-AFTER-WRITE so audit never logs a write that failed), `adr-check` (ADR-001/002/004/008/010/013/015/019/029).</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark 031 ✅. Update `current-task.md`: 031 complete; remaining Group D tasks (032, 033, 034) still in-flight or complete.</step>
    <step order="11">Commit + push branch update. Note any contract refinements for downstream Phase 4 wiring.</step>
  </steps>

