  <notes>
    Resume wiring (`OnGateApprovalRecordUpdated`) is intentionally stub-only here. Phase 4 task 042 wires it into the orchestrator's run-resumption logic; that task may add a Dataverse webhook endpoint OR consume a plugin → BFF callback. ADR-002 governs plugin code if added (thin, no HTTP/Graph).

    The `IIdempotencyService` is the same one used for `ScheduledActionDispatchJobHandler` (ADR-004); reuse via constructor injection. Idempotency key shape: `gate:{ActionRunId}:{ToolDispatchId}`.

    AUDIT-AFTER-WRITE ordering matters: if the Dataverse create succeeds but the audit write fails, log + raise — never the other way. The orchestrator MUST observe the actual world state, not just the audit log.
  </notes>

